Description: Papyrus (two fragments); Demotic literary text (previously unknown) with narrative about an upset pharaoh, who is told a narrative about the condemnation of Djed-hor; one side only. Same papyrus as EA 69532.
Curator's comments: Published by John Tait 'Pa-di-pep tells Pharaoh the Story of the Condemnation of Djed-hor: Fragments of Demotic Narrative in the British Museum' . Enchoria 31 (2008/9|), 112-43.
